summary.p: The total number of folios is unknown; Writing surface: parchment; Shelfmark: "qāf 3" (Gotthelf-Bergsträßer-archives) according to A. Grohmann 1958, p. 216: shelfmark "maṣāḥif 387" of the Egyptian National Library; Lines per page: 18; Dimensions: unknown; Qurʾānic Text: Q 1:1-Q 2:49, Q 2:56-70, Q 2:73-74, Q 2:77-80, Q 2:82-262, Q 4:56-102, Q 4:104-121, Q 6:19-98, Q 7:86-89, Q 7:95-102, Q 7:112-123, Q 7:129-134, Q 7:139-143, Q 7:147-151, Q 7:155- Q 10:12, Q 10:17-51, Q 16:11-72, Q 16:77-86, Q 16:88- Q 17:55, Q 17:65-79, Q 20:3-Q 21:36, Q 21:39-57, Q 21,78-Q 21:112, Q 22:11-23, Q 22:35-Q 23:36, Q 23:69- Q 25:65, Q 25:73- Q 26:5, Q 31:15- Q 37:175, Q 38:6- Q 43:67, Q 43:78- Q 48:18, Q 63:8- Q 74:50, Q 83:3-19, Q 83:23-36, Q 85:12-Q 86:8, Q 86:12-Q 87:14, Q 89:15- Q 92:2, Q 92:7-Q 100:2, Q 100:5-Q 101:11, Q 102:3-Q 104:8, Q 105:1-Q 107:6, Q 108:1-Q 110:3, Q 114:1-114:6; Script style: kūfī type C; Estimated date of production: 700-800; Provenance: Egypt.

This fragment was kept by the Khedival Library in Cairo, images were taken supposedly by Gotthelf Bergsträßer around 1930. As we do not know more about this fragment (dimensions, total amount of folios), we publish the 471 images of this codex as given in Bergsträßer's archives, attributing numbers in the order of the Qurʾānic text. The two images listed under no. 0 ("zero") contain a colophon page.
